author: Russell Brand
description:
Chinese scientists are building a humanoid “pregnancy robot” — a machine designed to gestate and give birth. At a time of war, despair, and cultural breakdown, why is energy spent on replacing motherhood with mechanized wombs? Is this really innovation, or the commodification of life itself? Beyond the sci-fi headlines lies a deeper agenda: fear, distraction, and the steady erosion of our humanity, unless we awaken to a higher truth before reality itself is engineered away.
[UNPACKED]
